               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Nuzhat al-arvāḥ by Mīr Fakhr al-Sādāt al-Ḥusaynī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1374x-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>The well-known compendium on Sufism in refined prose and verse by Rukn al-Dīn Ḥusayn ibn ʿĀlim ibn Abū al-Ḥasan al-Ḥusaynī al-Ghūrī known as Mīr Fakhr al-Sādāt al-Ḥusaynī (d. circa 720/1320). 
</p>
                        <p>The work was completed in 711/1311-2, when the author was aged 40. 
The treatise is divided into twenty-eight chapters termed faṣl. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 119r): completed by Mawlānā Yūnus resident of the mawz̤aʿ Pindī Shaykh Sulaymān Bhattī (?), at midday prayers, Wednesday, […] Muḥarram 1038/September 1628, written for the salvation of faith. 
Dense annotations throughout with a dated note at the end (f. 119v): notes based on the commentary or sharḥ by ʿAbd al-Vāḥid Ibrāhīm al-Ḥusaynī [Bilgrāmī] completed 985/1577, corrected from beginning to end by (erased text) [Ḥusām al-Dīn], 25 Shaʿbān in RY 2 [of Emperor Muḥammad Shāh], equating to 1132/2 July 1720. </p>
                        <p>Intermittent foliation in pencil. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacking original binding. 
</p>
                        <p>Later binding damaged (front board only of deep brown leather) and paper dust wrapper (BEIC legal publication on Regulation XVIII for 1817); torn and stained. 
</p>
                        <p>This copy is in very poor condition: unbound folios of brittle paper scarred by stains, cropped, wormholes and later repairs with paper patches. </p>
                     </note>
